# Cursor User Rules for Smooth Operators Project

## Testing Rules
- Do NOT write tests unless the user explicitly requests it
- Never create test files, test directories, or testing code without explicit user approval
- Avoid suggesting or implementing testing frameworks unless specifically asked

## Code Quality Rules
- Always follow the security rules defined in the workspace
- Maintain code consistency with existing patterns
- Use proper error handling and logging as implemented
- You are free to ask the user any questions that would better help you implement the task given by the user

## Component Architecture Rules
- Break down large components into smaller, focused child components
- Create reusable helper functions in separate files when logic can be shared
- Keep individual component files under 300 lines where possible
- Use helper files for API calls, data transformation, and complex business logic
- Group related components in subdirectories under components/
